             version of Maslow's hierarchy of needs</li>
            <li>More on why this is both relevant and sad later on</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Felt that I possessed many but not all of the characterisitics
         exhibited by Maslow's "self-actualizers" (self-actualised persons)</li>
        <li>Returned to work and shared at least some of my findings</li>
        <li>My perception of how I was treated at work was different to how it
         was before "Day 1"</li>
        <li>It's very much worth mentioning that I could not have asked for a
         better employer throughout</li>
        <li>Humbled... but only for a time</li>
        <li>I was [un]knowingly fluctuating between levels (conflict, split)
